  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Benson Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Jdg 20:26",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Jdg 20:26",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "All the people went up — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Not only all the warriors, but other people. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "And wept, and sat before the Lord — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Sensible of their not having been before truly humbled for their sins, which they seem now to discover to have been the cause of their ill success. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "And fasted that day until even — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "That they might afflict their souls, and become truly penitent. This they had not done before, at least not with such seriousness as they now did. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "And offered burnt-offerings — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "To make atonement to God for their own sins, and to offer to him solemn supplications for the pardon of them. Which things also they had neglected before. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "And peace-offerings — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "To bless God for sparing so many of them, whereas he might justly have cut them all off when their brethren were slain: to implore his assistance, yea, and to give thanks for the victory which now they were confident he would give them.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
