  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Pulpit Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verse 26.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Then all the children of Israel, and all the people",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", etc. Observe the word ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "all",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", twice repeated, as showing how the whole congregation was roused and stirred to a man by this second reverse. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "The",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "people",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", as distinguished from ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "the men of Israel",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", the army, probably means the non-fighting people, the aged, the infirm, women, etc. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "The house of God",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". Render, as in ver. 18 (see note), ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "Bethel. Sat there",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "Bethel. ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "cmt_word",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "Sat there",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". Sitting with the Jews, especially on the ground, was the attitude of grief and mourning (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Job 2:13",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Isaiah 47:1, 5",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Lamentations 2:10",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", etc.). The Jews at the present day often sit on the ground at the place of wailing in Jerusalem. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Before the Lord",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "i.e.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " before the tabernacle (see ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Judges 11:11",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", note), ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Fasted until evening",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The usual time for terminating a fast among the Jews, as at the present day among Mahomedans. For similar fasts on solemn occasions of national guilt or grief, see ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Samuel 7:6",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
