        "text": "Joel 1:14",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", etc. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Peace offerings",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". Usually thank offerings (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Leviticus 3",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Leviticus 7:11, 12",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), but applicable to any voluntary sacrifice of which the flesh might be eaten the same day, or the day following, by the offerer (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Leviticus 7:15, 16",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). Doubtless the people at the close of their fast ate the flesh of these peace offerings. Judges 20:26",
        "children": []
